This is a textbook case of **coverage-without-verification**. Every production method is called (→ 95% line coverage), but almost nothing is actually asserted. Here's the severity-ranked audit:

---

## 🔴 Critical — No assertion at all (tests can never fail)

These tests exercise code but verify **nothing**. Bugs here ship silently.

### 1. `AddProduct_Works` (line 17)
Calls `AddProduct` but never checks the product was persisted.
```csharp
// FIX:
_catalog.AddProduct(product);
var stored = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNotNull(stored);
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", stored.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, stored.Price);
```

### 2. `UpdatePrice_Works` (line 32)
Calls `UpdatePrice` but never checks the price changed.
```csharp
// FIX:
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
```

### 3. `RemoveProduct_Works` (line 38)
Calls `RemoveProduct` but never checks the product is gone.
```csharp
// FIX:
_catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
```

### 4. `GetProductCount_Works` (line 63)
Calls `GetProductCount` on an **empty** catalog and doesn't even capture or assert the result.
```csharp
// FIX:
Assert.AreEqual(0, _catalog.GetProductCount());
_catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
Assert.AreEqual(1, _catalog.GetProductCount());
```

### 5. `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (line 68)
Applies a 10% discount but never checks that prices were reduced.
```csharp
// FIX:
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);
Assert.AreEqual(8.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")!.Price);
Assert.AreEqual(17.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-002")!.Price);
```

### 6. `ImportFromCsv_Works` (line 84)
Imports CSV but never checks any product was created.
```csharp
// FIX:
_catalog.ImportFromCsv("SKU-001,Widget,9.99");
var p = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNotNull(p);
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", p.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, p.Price);
```

---

## 🟠 High — Weak assertions (assert only non-null, not correctness)

These tests won't catch wrong data — only outright crashes.

### 7. `GetProduct_Works` (line 23)
Asserts `IsNotNull` but never checks the returned product has the right SKU, name, or price. Any non-null object passes.
```csharp
